and procedure apply. The section provides that any drug paraphernalia involved in a violation of the section is subject to seizure and forfeiture upon the conviction of a person for such violation. Conviction of a violator is therefore a prerequisite to seizure and forfeiture. The section incorporates neither the customs laws, supplemental rules, nor any criminal forfeiture procedures.
Based on the lack of legislative guidance in this matter, the United States Attorneys' Offices are required to consult with the Asset Forfeiture Office prior to seeking seizure or forfeiture of property under the Mail Order Drug Paraphernalia Control Act. The Asset Forfeiture Office will work with the seizing agencies to develop consistent policies and procedures relating to the seizure and forfeiture of drug paraphernalia.
